    "This issue is an example of the \"halo effect,\" a well-known cognitive bias where an individual's specific positive traits (e.g., eloquence) are mistakenly interpreted as evidence of a general \"goodness\" that extends beyond these specific traits [22].",
    "In the case of an LLM, the quality of the presentation may be unconsciously assumed to match the veracity of the content.",
